body:
# Prisma Client

Prisma Client is a type-safe query builder generated from your [[prisma/schema]]. It provides a fluent API for all CRUD operations, relation queries, transactions, and raw SQL.

## Setup

```bash
# Install packages
npm install @prisma/client
npm install prisma --save-dev

# Generate the client (run after every schema change)
npx prisma generate
```

## Instantiation

```typescript
import { PrismaClient } from '@prisma/client';

const prisma = new PrismaClient();
```

## Singleton Pattern (Required for Production)

Avoid creating multiple `PrismaClient` instances â€” each opens its own connection pool:

```typescript
// lib/prisma.ts
import { PrismaClient } from '@prisma/client';

const globalForPrisma = globalThis as unknown as { prisma: PrismaClient };

export const prisma = globalForPrisma.prisma || new PrismaClient();

if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') globalForPrisma.prisma = prisma;
```

This is critical in Next.js and other hot-reloading environments where modules are re-evaluated.

## CRUD Operations

See [[prisma/client/queries]] for comprehensive query patterns.

```typescript
// Create
const user = await prisma.user.create({
  data: { email: 'alice@example.com', name: 'Alice' },
});

// Read
const user = await prisma.user.findUnique({ where: { id: 1 } });
const users = await prisma.user.findMany({ where: { role: 'ADMIN' } });

// Update
const updated = await prisma.user.update({
  where: { id: 1 },
  data: { name: 'Alice Updated' },
});

// Delete
const deleted = await prisma.user.delete({ where: { id: 1 } });

// Upsert
const user = await prisma.user.upsert({
  where: { email: 'alice@example.com' },
  update: { name: 'Alice Updated' },
  create: { email: 'alice@example.com', name: 'Alice' },
});
```

## Relation Queries

See [[prisma/client/relations]] for detailed relation patterns.

```typescript
// Include related records
const userWithPosts = await prisma.user.findUnique({
  where: { id: 1 },
  include: { posts: true },
});

// Select specific fields
const userEmail = await prisma.user.findUnique({
  where: { id: 1 },
  select: { email: true, posts: { select: { title: true } } },
});

// Nested create
const userWithPost = await prisma.user.create({
  data: {
    email: 'bob@example.com',
    name: 'Bob',
    posts: {
      create: [{ title: 'First Post' }, { title: 'Second Post' }],
    },
  },
  include: { posts: true },
});
```

## Transactions

```typescript
// Sequential transaction (batch of operations)
const [posts, count] = await prisma.$transaction([
  prisma.post.findMany({ where: { published: true } }),
  prisma.post.count(),
]);

// Interactive transaction (with custom logic)
const result = await prisma.$transaction(async (tx) => {
  const sender = await tx.account.update({
    data: { balance: { decrement: 100 } },
    where: { email: 'alice@example.com' },
  });
  if (sender.balance < 0) throw new Error('Insufficient funds');
  return await tx.account.update({
    data: { balance: { increment: 100 } },
    where: { email: 'bob@example.com' },
  });
}, {
  maxWait: 5000,
  timeout: 10000,
  isolationLevel: 'Serializable',
});
```

## Raw SQL

```typescript
// Parameterized query (safe from SQL injection)
const users = await prisma.$queryRaw`SELECT * FROM "User" WHERE email = ${email}`;

// Parameterized execute
const count = await prisma.$executeRaw`UPDATE "User" SET name = ${name} WHERE id = ${id}`;
```

**Never** use `$queryRawUnsafe` or `$executeRawUnsafe` with user input â€” they are vulnerable to SQL injection.

## Logging

```typescript
const prisma = new PrismaClient({
  log: ['query', 'info', 'warn', 'error'],
});

// Event-based logging
const prisma = new PrismaClient({
  log: [{ level: 'query', emit: 'event' }],
});
prisma.$on('query', (e) => {
  console.log(`Query: ${e.query} â€” Duration: ${e.duration}ms`);
});
```

## Connection Management

```typescript
// Explicit connect (optional â€” lazy connects on first query)
await prisma.$connect();

// Disconnect when shutting down
await prisma.$disconnect();
```

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|--------|
| `DATABASE_URL` | Connection string for the database |
